-- Magnitude 6.5 earthquake strikes northwestern Peru -USGS
-- By Paul Simao
-- Sat Mar 15, 2014 08:04PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, March 15 (Reuters) - A magnitude 6.5 earthquake struck northwestern Peru on Saturday, the U.S. Geological Survey reported.

The quake's epicenter was 26 miles (42 km) south-southwest of Piura and it occurred at a depth of 7.2 miles (12 km), the USGS said.